    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="847"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">919.534/7–251: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic and Consular Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d847fn1">Sent for action to Algiers, Karachi, Istanbul,
                        Saigon, Tokyo, <gloss target="#t_HICOG1">HICOG</gloss> (Germany), Calcutta,
                        and Belfast; sent for information to Hong Kong.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-02T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 2, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Panama Govt authorizes you acting for it re shipping pick up papers and
                    withhold sailing permit any vessel Pan registry destined North Korean or Chi
                    commie ports. Pan Govt suggests you base action on need verify validity ship’s
                    registry. Interested local auths may be informed any action taken pursuant this
                    auth.</p>
                <p>Report cases with name of vessel, registry nr and call letters to Pan Govt
                    through Amembassy Pan with info copy <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> and
                    await instrs which will be sent by Pan Govt through <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss>. Tokyo and <gloss target="#t_HICOG1">HICOG</gloss> shld advise
                    appropriate Consulates their jurisdictions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
